This paper discusses a security architecture for user space privilege separation on x86 architecture, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and operating systems (cs.OS). The paper also discusses the implementation of the architecture, which involves software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of cryptographic keys, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.AR).
